# Trivy ignore file — accepted / unfixable findings
#
# Format: one GHSA or CVE ID per line, optionally with an expiry date:
#   GHSA-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx exp:2026-12-31
#
# Before adding an entry here:
#   1. Confirm the finding has no sane fix (e.g. the "fix" would be a major
#      downgrade that breaks the app).
#   2. Document WHY it is accepted.
#   3. Set an expiry date so the suppress is re-evaluated periodically.

# postcss < 8.5.10 — XSS via unescaped </style> in bundled Next.js postcss.
# The only fix npm offers is `npm audit fix --force` which downgrades Next.js
# to 9.3.3 — a 6-major-version downgrade that is not acceptable.
# Re-evaluate when Next.js ships a patch that bundles postcss >= 8.5.10.
# GHSA: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93
GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93 exp:2026-11-25
CVE-2026-41305 exp:2026-11-25

# @hono/node-server < 1.19.13 — middleware bypass via repeated slashes in
# serveStatic. This is a devDependency of @prisma/dev (internal Prisma
# tooling). The only fix downgrades prisma from 7.x to 6.x — a breaking
# change for this project. Re-evaluate when Prisma 7.x ships with a fixed
# @hono/node-server version.
